---

<BaseLayout title="Mike Abebe & Abebe Ventures | Who Is Abebe?">

  <Header>
    <Fragment slot="title">Mike Abebe & Abebe Ventures</Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      A central dossier on the person, company, entities, projects,
      249 Milton Ave SE, and Waynesboro property references.
    </Fragment>
  </Header>

  <main class="article-wrap">
    <article class="article-body report-page mike-report-page">

      <p class="lede">
        This page collects source material connected to Mike Abebe and Abebe
        Ventures, including public-facing images, company claims, project
        snapshots, Georgia entity records, address references, and Waynesboro
        property records captured for review.
      </p>

      <div class="notice-box">
        <strong>Scope:</strong>
        This profile is based on public records and archived source material.
        It separates documented references from observations and open questions.
      </div>

      <h2>Why This Page Matters</h2>

      <p>
        Abebe Ventures is now the public-facing umbrella for a broad set of
        development claims: Atlanta projects, St. George Crossing in Waynesboro,
        the 249 Milton Ave / former Yellow Cab site, and a company biography
        claiming more than 1,000 homes across multiple cities. This report keeps
        those company claims next to the entity records, archived partner pages,
        and property records needed to evaluate them.
      </p>

      <div class="fact-grid dossier-grid">
        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Person</span>
          <p>
            Mike Abebe is identified through current Abebe.com material, archived
            Direct Invest material, Ensley Rising archive material, and local
            reporting tied to St. George Crossing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Company</span>
          <p>
            Abebe Ventures presents the active public-facing development brand,
            with project pages, leadership claims, and 249 Milton Ave listed in
            the company record.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Entities</span>
          <p>
            Georgia entity records in this archive show multiple Abebe-linked
            LLCs and corporations using 249 Milton Ave SE as a principal office
            or address reference.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Image Trail</h2>

      <div class="portrait-pair">
        <figure class="report-figure portrait-figure">
          <img
            src="/images/entities/mike-abebe-headshot.png"
            alt="Mike Abebe current Abebe.com headshot"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Current Abebe.com leadership headshot. This appears to be a newer,
            more polished image used by Abebe Ventures on the updated company site.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="report-figure portrait-figure">
          <img
            src="/images/entities/mike-abebe-portrait.jpg"
            alt="Older Mike Abebe portrait"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Older portrait used elsewhere in the archive and retained as a
            separate visual reference from the current Abebe.com headshot.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="report-figure portrait-figure">
          <img
            src="/images/entities/mike-abebe-otv-interview.jpg"
            alt="Mike Abebe OTV interview still"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Still image captured from an
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PHlxiRJsMTw&t=29s" target="_blank">
              OTV interview video
            </a>
            used as another public-facing visual reference for Mike Abebe.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <h2>Current Abebe.com Leadership Page</h2>

      <p>
        The current Abebe Ventures leadership page now gives a fuller public
        biography for Mike Abebe and uses a newer, more groomed headshot. That
        matters because earlier identification relied heavily on archived
        websites, older images, and hard-to-find image references before the
        company updated its own public profile.
      </p>

      <p>
        Abebe.com states that Mike Abebe's real estate work grew from a single
        Bankhead Highway convenience store into more than 1,000 homes across
        Atlanta, Baltimore, and Minneapolis, with nearly 70 percent described as
        qualifying as affordable housing. This is included here as a current
        company claim that should be compared against project records, permits,
        affordability restrictions, and local housing documentation.
      </p>

      <a class="document-row" href="https://www.abebe.com/leadership" target="_blank">
        <span>Current Website</span>
        <strong>Abebe Ventures Leadership Page</strong>
        <p>
          Current company page identifying Mike Abebe and describing his career,
          housing output, and affordable-housing claim.
        </p>
      </a>

      <h2>Archived Abebe Holdings Origin Story</h2>

      <p>
        A Wayback Machine capture from April 24, 2009 preserves an earlier
        Abebe.com "About Us" page for Abebe Homes / Abebe Holdings. That page
        gives an older company-origin narrative: Michael Abebe starting from a
        Bankhead Highway convenience store in 1997, then moving into property
        ownership, renovation, residential development, commercial and industrial
        space, parking, gas stations, and convenience-store development.
      </p>

      <p>
        The archived page described Abebe Holdings as beginning with a
        "single venture in a small convenience store" and later listed Abebe
        Holdings as the parent company of Rosewood Funding, Rosewood Properties,
        Premium Parking, Abebe Westside Development, Abebe Homes, and Hagmch
        Construction. It also said Abebe Homes had renovated and built more than
        200 projects in metro Atlanta by that point.
      </p>

      <p>
        This archived company history matters because the newer Abebe.com
        leadership page repeats the convenience-store origin story but expands
        the scale claim to more than 1,000 homes across Atlanta, Baltimore, and
        Minneapolis. The archive can now compare the 2009 company narrative
        against the current Abebe Ventures biography and project list.
      </p>

      <a
        class="document-row"
        href="https://web.archive.org/web/20090424000000/http://www.abebe.com/aboutus.php"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <span>Wayback Capture</span>
        <strong>Abebe.com About Us - April 24, 2009</strong>
        <p>
          Archived Abebe Holdings / Abebe Homes page describing the Bankhead
          Highway origin story, early company structure, and Atlanta
          revitalization framing.
        </p>
      </a>

      <h2>249 Milton Ave SE</h2>

      <p>
        The Atlanta address at 249 Milton Ave SE appears repeatedly in the
        public records file as a principal office or address reference for
        multiple Abebe-linked entities.
      </p>

      <div class="milton-comparison">
        <figure class="report-figure">
          <img
            src="/images/properties/249-milton-ave-hq-google-maps.png"
            alt="249 Milton Ave SE Google Maps screenshot"
          />
          <figcaption>Google Maps screenshot of 249 Milton Ave SE, Atlanta, Georgia.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="report-figure">
          <img
            src="/docs/projects/249-milton-abebe-project.png"
            alt="Abebe.com 249 Milton Ave project snapshot"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Abebe.com project snapshot showing the proposed 249 Milton Ave
            redevelopment rendering and company description.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <h2>249 Milton Ave Redevelopment Claim</h2>

      <p>
        Current Abebe.com project material describes 249 Milton Ave as a planned
        15-story mixed-use development with approximately 250 residential units
        and ground-floor retail. The company copy says the site was formerly the
        Yellow Cab headquarters and frames the proposed yellow exterior as a
        tribute to that history.
      </p>

      <p>
        The comparison is stark: the same 249 Milton Ave address appears across
        Abebe-linked entity filings, Yellow Cab references, and the Abebe
        Ventures company address, while the current Abebe.com rendering presents
        the former taxi-company site as a large, bright yellow residential
        building.
      </p>

      <div class="notice-box">
        <strong>Open question:</strong>
        The current Abebe.com 249 Milton Ave project snapshot should be compared
        against property records, permitting, zoning, BeltLine-overlay material,
        and older sale/listing records for the former Yellow Cab property.
      </div>

      <h2>Atlanta Development Context</h2>

      <p>
        The Atlanta side of the research file matters because Abebe Ventures
        presents itself as an Atlanta-based real estate development company, lists
        249 Milton Ave SE as its address, and shows multiple Atlanta-area projects
        alongside St. George Crossing.
      </p>

      <div class="document-list">
        <a class="document-row" href="https://www.abebe.com/" target="_blank">
          <span>Website</span>
          <strong>Abebe Ventures</strong>
          <p>
            Public company website listing Abebe Ventures, 249 Milton Ave SE,
            St. George Crossing, and Atlanta-area development projects.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a
          class="document-row"
          href="https://www.wsbtv.com/news/local/atlanta/developer-hopes-create-city-within-city-along-atlantas-beltline/GZLWCGFOZFC2DCQFPD4RZSH5SM/"
          target="_blank"
        >
          <span>Atlanta Reporting</span>
          <strong>WSB-TV: Developer hopes to create a city within the city along Atlanta's BeltLine</strong>
          <p>
            April 3, 2025 WSB-TV coverage of Mike Abebe's proposed large-scale
            Sylvan Road/BeltLine-area development in Southwest Atlanta.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a
          class="document-row"
          href="https://www.facebook.com/GAFollowers/posts/developer-mike-abebe-plans-to-revitalize-25-acres-along-the-beltline-in-southwes/1115869937009246/"
          target="_blank"
        >
          <span>Social Post</span>
          <strong>GA Followers post on Mike Abebe BeltLine-area plans</strong>
          <p>
            Social-media reference to the proposed 25-acre Southwest Atlanta
            revitalization plan.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <figure class="report-figure">
        <img
          src="/images/articles/mike-abebe-wsbtv-interview.png"
          alt="Mike Abebe WSB-TV interview screenshot"
        />
        <figcaption>Captured WSB-TV interview image associated with Mike Abebe's Atlanta development coverage.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2>Abebe Ventures Project Claims</h2>

      <p>
        The updated Abebe.com site now lists multiple development projects. The
        archive preserves those company-published pages as screenshots so the
        claims can be compared against public records over time.
      </p>

      <div class="mini-project-grid">
        {abebeProjectHighlights.map((project) => (
          <a class="mini-project-card" href={project.snapshotPath} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
            <img src={project.snapshotPath} alt={`${project.name} Abebe.com project snapshot`} loading="lazy" />
            <span>{project.location}</span>
            <strong>{project.name}</strong>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>

      <a class="section-card feature-card" href="/projects">
        <span>Project Archive</span>
        <h3>All Abebe.com Project Snapshots</h3>
        <p>
          Review the captured Abebe.com development pages for Sylvan Rd,
          St. George Crossing, 249 Milton Ave, Donald Lee Hollowell projects,
          Rockbridge Road, Magnolia Street, Tucker Ave, Vine Line, and Lee Street.
        </p>
      </a>

      <h2>LLCs and Entities in the Research File</h2>

      <div class="wide-table">
        <table class="report-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>State</th>
              <th>Entity</th>
              <th>Control No.</th>
              <th>Business Type</th>
              <th>Principal Office</th>
              <th>Registered Agent</th>
              <th>Status</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            {miltonEntities.map((entity) => (
              <tr>
                <td>{entity.state}</td>
                <td>{entity.name}</td>
                <td>{entity.controlNumber}</td>
                <td>{entity.businessType}</td>
                <td>{entity.principalOffice}</td>
                <td>{entity.registeredAgent}</td>
                <td>{entity.status}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>Waynesboro Property References</h2>

      <p>
        A qPublic capture in the archive references Waynesboro properties tied
        to Abebe St George-related records, including parcels in and around the
        central Waynesboro street grid.
      </p>

      <div class="notice-box">
        <strong>Condition note:</strong>
        Several listed parcels appear to sit in the heart of Waynesboro, including
        Liberty Street and Shadrack Street properties. Local review indicates
        some of these properties may be abandoned, vacant, or dormant after purchase.
        Dated photos, code records, parcel history, or other source material
        would help distinguish visual observation from verified property condition.
      </div>

      <figure class="report-figure">
        <img
          src="/images/properties/abebe-st-george-properties-waynesboro-qpublic.png"
          alt="qPublic screenshot of Abebe St George properties in Waynesboro"
        />
        <figcaption>qPublic screenshot referencing Abebe St George property records in Waynesboro, Georgia.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2>Waynesboro Parcels Listed in qPublic Capture</h2>

      <div class="wide-table">
        <table class="report-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Parcel ID</th>
              <th>Record ID</th>
              <th>Owner Name</th>
              <th>Address</th>
              <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            {waynesboroProperties.map((property) => (
              <tr>
                <td>{property.parcelId}</td>
                <td>{property.recordId}</td>
                <td>{property.owner}</td>
                <td>{property.address}</td>
                <td>{property.description}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>Working Notes</h2>

      <div class="fact-grid">
        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Verified</span>
          <p>
            The archive contains public-facing images, address screenshots,
            Atlanta development coverage, and entity references connected to
            Mike Abebe and Abebe-related LLCs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Observation</span>
          <p>
            249 Milton Ave SE appears across multiple Abebe-related entity records
            and is also listed on the public Abebe Ventures website. Waynesboro
            property records also place Abebe St George Ventures LLC on parcels
            in central Waynesboro. The updated Abebe.com leadership page now
            now uses a newer Mike Abebe headshot, while the older archive image
            remains useful for connecting Direct Invest and Ensley Rising material
            to the same person.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Open Question</span>
          <p>
            The Waynesboro property picture still needs parcel-by-parcel
            documentation with owner, parcel ID, acreage, address, purchase date,
            condition notes, dated photos, and source date. The current Abebe.com
            claim of more than 1,000 homes, with nearly 70 percent qualifying as
            affordable housing, also needs underlying project-level documentation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .portrait-figure {
    max-width: 360px;
  }

  .portrait-pair {
    align-items: start;
    display: grid;
    gap: 24px;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    margin: 34px 0 48px;
  }

  .portrait-pair .report-figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .portrait-pair img {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    object-fit: cover;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .mike-report-page {
    max-width: 940px;
  }

  .dossier-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .milton-comparison {
    display: grid;
    gap: 22px;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    margin: 34px 0 48px;
  }

  .milton-comparison .report-figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .milton-comparison img {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
    object-fit: contain;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .mini-project-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 16px;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    margin: 28px 0 32px;
  }

  .mini-project-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: inherit;
    display: block;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .mini-project-card img {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
    background: #f2f2f2;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: block;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: top;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .mini-project-card span,
  .mini-project-card strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
    padding: 0 12px;
  }

  .mini-project-card span {
    color: var(--red);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-top: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .mini-project-card strong {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    padding-bottom: 14px;
    padding-top: 6px;
  }

  .wide-table {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 28px 0 50px;
  }

  .wide-table .report-table {
    table-layout: fixed;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .wide-table .report-table th,
  .wide-table .report-table td {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    padding: 8px;
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
  }

  .wide-table .report-table th:nth-child(1),
  .wide-table .report-table td:nth-child(1) {
    width: 5%;
  }

  .wide-table .report-table th:nth-child(2),
  .wide-table .report-table td:nth-child(2) {
    width: 20%;
  }

  .wide-table .report-table th:nth-child(3),
  .wide-table .report-table td:nth-child(3) {
    width: 10%;
  }

  .wide-table .report-table th:nth-child(4),
  .wide-table .report-table td:nth-child(4) {
    width: 18%;
  }

  .wide-table .report-table th:nth-child(5),
  .wide-table .report-table td:nth-child(5) {
    width: 22%;
  }

  .wide-table .report-table th:nth-child(6),
  .wide-table .report-table td:nth-child(6) {
    width: 14%;
  }

  .wide-table .report-table th:nth-child(7),
  .wide-table .report-table td:nth-child(7) {
    width: 11%;
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .mike-report-page {
      max-width: 780px;
    }

    .dossier-grid,
    .mini-project-grid,
    .portrait-pair,
    .milton-comparison {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .wide-table .report-table {
      min-width: 860px;
    }
  }
</style>
